title: For Sale:  Norinco AK47 Underfolder
location: Van Wert, OH, Fort Wayne, Indiana
postcontent:
I have for sale a nice early Norinco Underfolder AK.  This one was imported right when the ban first happened.  I think it was made in 1987 or 1988.  I want $600 for it.  The rifle looks about new.  I doubt it was shot very  much.  I do not have a magazine though, I did not receive any when I got it.

This AK was made as a preban but was caught in customs when the ban went into effect in 1989.  So the markings had to be removed so it could be legally sold.  Only one batch of rifles were done this way.  They removed the bayonet lug, and also the threads for the muzzle break and attached the muzzle break with an adaptor.   So if you collect AK's, this is a rare one.

My buddy was going to buy it, but he can't come up with the cash for a while.

Here is a link to AR15, where we were discussing what this AK is:

http://www.ar15.com/forums/t_4_64/141415_Is_this_Norinco_Pre_Ban__GLNIC_LA_CA.html

I would consider trades for USGI stuff, or WWII German and Japanese items as well.

I have for sale a German Luger.  This was a bring back that I purchased from an estate.  It's a WWI rebuild that was rebuilt in the 1930's for the build up of the German military.  There is no date on the top of the chamber because they were not allowed to make German Lugers with the Treaty of Versailles in 9mm.  So these were made in violation fo the Tready and not dated, so they couldn't prove when they were made.  

This is an interesting variation of a luger and pretty hard to find.  I'm looking for $1000 and would consider trades for other WWII items.  Or even newer stuff depending on what you have.

postcontent:
I have a marlin model 60 semi auto 22 LR for sale/ trade. The magazine tube holds 17, these are no longer available. it is the "pre-ban" model, not trying to make it sound like an AR, just letting you know what it is. i think the cap is now 13, but could be wrong on this; i do know that you can no longer get the 17 shot tube. Shoots straight and true. These are great little shooters, but I am way heavy on the long guns and I prefer 22 pistols for just plinking and fun.  it is the 60 with the checkered stock and the squirrel etched in the stock, not going to call it a collector’s item but you don’t see this model 60 very often; usually just a standard walnut stock. would make a great starter for a youngster wanting to get in to squirrel hunting or just getting involved in the sport of target shooting. Crown of barrel looks good and bluing is probably 85% +, but i am not a firearms appraiser. the riflings are impeccable and the bore is bright. the rifle does have some scuffs, but nothing major; i mention only because if you are looking for something brand new i want to let you know up front it has been used. let me know what you have for trade, all i can say is no, again though, I am looking to eliminate some long guns. pics will be up soon. email if interested, if you leave a number and do not want to be called after a certain time put that in the email, because i am up late. Willing to go 20, maybe 30 minutes from zip code 45102, for trade of interest possibly further. also willing to go  further for Military and law enforcement, wont go too far, as it is not an expensive item. Thanks for your interest
Jack
